{
  "bookId": "heshanggong-laozi",
  "num": 43,
  "title": "第四十三章（徧用）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "天下之至柔，馳騁天下之至堅。"
    },
    {
      "text": "無有入無間。"
    },
    {
      "text": "吾是以知無為之有益。"
    },
    {
      "text": "不言之教，"
    },
    {
      "text": "無為之益，"
    },
    {
      "text": "天下希及之。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 14
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "至柔者，水也。至堅者，金石也。 水能貫堅入剛，無所不通。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "無有謂道也。 道無形質，故能出入無間，通神明濟群生也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "吾見道無為而萬物自化成，是以知無為之有益於人也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "法道不言，師之以身。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "法道無為，治身則有益於精神，治國則有益於萬民，不勞煩也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "天下，人主也。 希能有及道無為之治身治國也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
